column3: str
Lali-just the sinner I've been looking for-ho.
Another one of those recording devices has arrived from Konogg. Seems the lad has more he wants to say to you. Here.
When you have a moment, be sure to see what's on it.
(-???-)You there!
Yes, the two of you! What are you doin', talkin' and noddin' suspiciously!? What are you up to!?
<gasp> You're conspirin' to take over the village, aren't you!? Just like those murderous machines!
Huh? What am I...? What did I just...? Unnngh, my head...
Something's not right with Glagg. And it's not quite the same sort of “not right” what follows a few too many casks of ale...
Well, whatever it is, it's nothing you need to worry about. I'll take care of it.
Now then, was there something else you needed?
What will you say?
Is there anything I can help with?
How's the rebuilding coming along?
Hmmm, well...
(-???-)Excuse me...
You... What do you want? If you're here to mock us, have done with it and leave us be.
N-No, I'm not here to mock you. On the contrary, I want to join you.

I'm usually not one to get involved, preferring to observe from a safe distance while making the occasional comment to remind people of my presence. But seeing how hard you've been working for the village, I couldn't help but want to make myself useful for a change.
Well, we could certainly use all the help we can get... What say you, <Split(<Highlight>ObjectParameter(1)</Highlight>, ,1)/>? Shall we welcome him to the crew?
Thank you! I'm certain you won't regret it!
After that strangeness with Glagg, I wasn't sure what to expect from our dour friend, but it sure wasn't an offer of help.
Anyway, I'll find a moment to talk with the fellow about our plans. And when he's managed to settle in, you ought to have a word with him too.
But to answer your earlier question─there's nothing we need you for right now. Only a matter of time before we call on you again, though, so kick your feet up while you can.
To be deleted.
A weekly quest which continues the story is now available from the dour dwarf in Komra.
Lend your aid and help the dwarves of Komra to rebuild their home.
You obtain a message from Konogg.

The message can be viewed in your <UIForeground>F201F4</UIForeground><UIGlow>F201F5</UIGlow>Portable Archive<UIGlow>01</UIGlow><UIForeground>01</UIForeground>, which is available under Collection in the Duty section of the main menu.
